node.text: The living legend @MikeHornExplorer tells us about the horrible scenes he has witnessed during his adventures and the importance of the young generations in the race to save our planet ! We must all get together now and start moving, it’s time for action ! Our special thanks to @spgrytz for supporting our vision towards a sustainable environment! #DiscoverEarth

Exploring with @jacintashackleton: “If you haven’t already heard, sea turtles absolutely love to munch on jelly snacks, especially the coloured ones 💜 Unfortunately, it also means they frequently mistake plastic for their favourite food, so let’s keep it out of the ocean!” 

Would you go for a swim with this curious turtle? 🐢

#discoverearth with @jacintashackleton

node.text:
This must be the perfect hideaway 🌲😴 Would you sleep in this epic forest escape?

With its impressive size, it’s no wonder that Russia has incredibly diverse wildlife and landscapes – including forests filled with birch, pine and fir trees. The country’s more remote areas and preserved landscapes are also home to some unique species such as the Siberian tiger, amur leopard, Asian black bears and the Siberian bighorn sheep. 🐏

📍@neotipi, Russia 

🇷🇺 #discoverRussia with @tattivasilieva & @neotipi
